Telesat Canada: Private Company Information - Bloomberg










































  





















































































July 28, 2017 8:39 PM ET
Diversified Telecommunication Services

Company Overview of Telesat Canada



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Telesat Canada Ltd. provides satellite delivered communication services to broadcast, telecommunication, corporate, and government customers. The company’s satellite-based services allow DTH service providers to deliver television programming, audio, and information channels directly to customers’ homes; and enables broadcasters, cable networks, and DTH service providers to transmit television programming services. It also offers value-added services that include satellite capacity, digital encoding of video channels, authorization, and up linking and down linking services; and occasional use services for the broadcast of video news, sports, and live event coverage. In addition, the company ...
Telesat Canada Ltd. provides satellite delivered communication services to broadcast, telecommunication, corporate, and government customers. The company’s satellite-based services allow DTH service providers to deliver television programming, audio, and information channels directly to customers’ homes; and enables broadcasters, cable networks, and DTH service providers to transmit television programming services. It also offers value-added services that include satellite capacity, digital encoding of video channels, authorization, and up linking and down linking services; and occasional use services for the broadcast of video news, sports, and live event coverage. In addition, the company offers satellite capacity and end-to-end services comprising and space segment services and terrestrial facilities for broadband, Internet and cellular backhaul; rural telephony to telecommunications carriers and network services integrators; and fixed satellite services, as well as provides satellite operator services. Further, it provides Ka-band satellite services that provide two-way broadband Internet services; communications services for the oil and gas and mining industries; and maritime and aeronautical broadband communications services to commercial airplanes and vessels. The company also operates very small aperture terminal (VSAT) and hybrid VSAT/terrestrial networks, as well as provides end-to-end services, including installation and maintenance of the end user terminals, maintenance of the VSAT hubs, and provision of satellite capacity. It also offers various consulting services related to space and earth segments, government studies, satellite control services, and research and development. Telesat Canada Ltd. offers services worldwide primarily through direct sales force. The company was founded in 1969 and is based in Ottawa, Canada. Telesat Canada Ltd. operates as a subsidiary of Loral Space & Communications Inc.
Detailed Description


