Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2017. 

Telesat Canada Key Developments

Telesat Canada Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Second Quarter and Six Months Ended June 30, 2017
Jul 25 17
Telesat Canada reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the second quarter and six months ended June 30, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported revenue of CAD 225,982,000 against CAD 231,686,000 a year ago. Operating income was 119,291,000 against CAD 125,998,000 a year ago. Income before tax was CAD 165,400,000 against CAD 80,900,000 a year ago. Net income was CAD 147,634,000 against CAD 61,729,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was CAD 183,637,000 against CAD 191,105,000 a year ago. The decline in revenue was primarily due to short-term services provided to another satellite operator in the second quarter of 2016, partially offset by favorable foreign exchange rate changes on the conversion of U.S. dollar revenue, as the U.S. dollar was approximately 5% stronger on average against the Canadian dollar than it was during the second quarter of 2016.

For the six months, the company reported revenue of CAD 460,651,000 against CAD 466,619,000 a year ago. Operating income was 236,029,000 against CAD 248,685,000 a year ago. Income before tax was CAD 268,589,000 against CAD 338,196,000 a year ago. Net income was CAD 235,617,000 against CAD 299,095,000 a year ago. Net cash from operating activities was CAD 251,927,000 against CAD 265,485,000 a year ago. Purchase of other property and equipment was CAD 5,726,000 against CAD 3,785,000 a year ago. Purchase of intangible assets was CAD 12,653,000 against CAD 36,745,000 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was CAD 375,872,000 against CAD 382,096,000 a year ago.


Telesat Canada, Q2 2017 Earnings Call, Jul 26, 2017
Jul 20 17
Telesat Canada, Q2 2017 Earnings Call, Jul 26, 2017


Telesat Holdings Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017
May 4 17
Telesat Holdings Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company's revenue was CAD 234.669 million compared to CAD 234.933 million a year ago. Operating income was CAD 116.738 million compared to CAD 122.687 million a year ago. Income before tax was CAD 103.189 million compared to CAD 257.296 million a year ago. Net income was CAD 87.983 million compared to CAD 237.366 million a year ago. Net cash from operating activities was CAD 130.396 million compared to CAD 164.557 million a year ago. Purchase of other property and equipment was CAD 3.746 million compared to CAD 2.466 million a year ago. Purchase of intangible assets was CAD 7.205 million compared to CAD 31.240 a year ago. Adjusted EBITDA was CAD 192.235 million compared to CAD 190.991 million a year ago.


